Re: Proof-of-work difficulty increasing

Bitcointalk

2010-07-16 18:43:51 UTC - [11]Original Post

   Right, the difficulty adjustment is trying to keep it so the network as
   a whole generates an average of 6 blocks per hour.  The time for your
   block to mature will always be around 20 hours.
   The recent adjustment put us back to close to 6 blocks per hour again.
   Thereʼs a site where you can see the time between blocks, and since
   block 68545, itʼs been more like 10 minutes per block:
   [12]http://nullvoid.org/bitcoin/statistix.php
